## 2) Naming & Formatting

### Naming Conventions
- **HCL labels**: `snake_case` for resource/module/variable/output names
- **Cloud names/tags**: use `kebab-case` (e.g., `Name = "app-core-vpc"`)
- **Files**: conventional layout (`versions.tf`, `providers.tf`, `main.tf`, `variables.tf`, `outputs.tf`, `locals.tf`, `README.md`, `examples/`)

### Tagging (AWS example)
```hcl
locals {
  base_tags = {
    app         = var.app
    environment = var.environment
    owner       = var.owner
    managed_by  = "terraform"
  }
}

resource "aws_vpc" "this" {
  cidr_block           = var.vpc_cidr
  enable_dns_support   = true
  enable_dns_hostnames = true
  tags                 = merge(local.base_tags, { Name = "${var.app}-${var.environment}-vpc" })
}
```

### Formatting
- All generated code must be formatted as if `terraform fmt` has been run on it
- Use consistent indentation (2 spaces standard)
- Group related attributes logically (e.g., all `enable_*` flags together)

